Developer Terms of Use
des:
Say “Alexa, open Vision Australia” to learn about the many services and support that Vision Australia offers to people who are blind or have low vision, their family and carers. This includes useful information about:
• Eye conditions
• Getting around your home and neighbourhood
• Connecting with others
• Using technology
• The Talking Book Library
• The Vision Store
• Site locations and contact details

Among other features, the Skill provides an easy way to listen to your favourite Vision Australia Radio Station or Podcast.

Even if you cannot find the information you need, you can request a call back from Vision Australia from within the Skill.

For more information about Vision Australia and the Skill you can also call 1300 84 74 66 or email info@visionaustralia.org.

The information in this Skill is provided for informational and educational purposes only. It is not a substitute for professional medical advice, treatment or diagnosis. Call your doctor to receive medical advice. If you think you may have a medical emergency, please dial your local emergency response phone number.
